headline: P&G's innovation is 'carrying us through' uncertainty: CEO
summary: Procter & Gamble (PG) beat fiscal first quarter earnings expectations, the consumer brand publishing adjusted earnings of $1.99 per share (vs. estimates of $1.88) and revenue of $22.4 billion (vs. estimates of $22.2 billion). The parent company of Head & Shoulders and Tide Pods is warning of a challenging consumer environment ahead. Procter & Gamble CEO Jon Moeller sits down with Yahoo Finance executive editor Brian Sozzi to talk more about the state of the consumer amid geopolitical and trade headwinds and the company's growth in beauty and grooming businesses. Moeller will move into the role of executive chairman while handing over the chief executive role to COO Shailesh Jejurikar, effective January 1, 2026. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Opening Bid.

headline: P&G Stock Ticks Up on Earnings. Why Tariffs Are Still a Factor to Watch.
summary: Shares of  Procter & Gamble  ticked up Friday after the maker of consumer products reported better-than-expected quarterly earnings.  The company posted core earnings of $1.99 a share for its fiscal first quarter, surpassing analysts’ consensus estimates of $1.90.  The company’s beauty and grooming segments, which include brands like Head & Shoulders and Gillette, drove the solid results.
